## Pre-Report Checkpoint

Before writing the scan report, confirm ALL scan tools have completed.
If any tool shows "Pending" or is still running, **WAIT**. Do NOT write the report
with incomplete data. Record tools that crashed/timed out as "Error", not "Pending".

---

## Phase 5: Generate Scan Report

{{EVIDENCE_COLLECTION}}

**Compile all findings into a structured scan report.**

```bash
_EMDASH_BIN=$([ -d ~/.claude/skills/em-dash/bin ] && echo ~/.claude/skills/em-dash/bin || echo .claude/skills/em-dash/bin)
source <("$_EMDASH_BIN"/hipaa-slug 2>/dev/null || true)
_USER=$(whoami 2>/dev/null || echo "unknown")
_DATETIME=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)
_REPORT_PATH="$HOME/.em-dash/projects/${SLUG:-unknown}/${_USER}-soc2-scan-${_DATETIME}.md"
echo "REPORT_PATH: $_REPORT_PATH"
```

Write the report with SOC 2 Trust Service Criteria mappings:

```markdown
# SOC 2 Technical Scan Report
**Project:** [project name]
**Date:** [date]
**Framework:** SOC 2 Type II — Trust Service Criteria

## Requirement Mapping

| Criteria | Requirement | Status | Evidence |
|----------|-------------|--------|----------|
| CC6.1 | Logical Access Security | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
| CC6.3 | Role-Based Access | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
| CC6.6 | System Boundaries | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
| CC7.1 | Configuration Management | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
| CC7.2 | Monitoring | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
| CC7.3 | Incident Response | PASS/FAIL | [evidence] |
```

